Select the ROCm component categories you want to install. You can select
multiple components for a customized installation.

[H1]Component Categories:

[H2]core
    Core ROCm components required for basic ROCm functionality.
    Includes base libraries and runtime components.

[H2]core-dev
    Core development components for building ROCm applications.
    Includes development headers and libraries.

[H2]dev-tools
    Developer tools for ROCm application development and debugging.
    Includes profilers, debuggers, and development utilities.

[H2]opencl
    OpenCL runtime support for ROCm.
    Enables OpenCL applications to run on AMD GPUs.

[H2]core-sdk (Select All)
    Complete ROCm SDK with all components above.
    Selecting this option automatically includes core, core-dev, dev-tools,
    and opencl. Recommended for full ROCm development environment.

[H1]Usage:

You can select individual components for a customized installation, or
select 'core-sdk' to install all components at once.

The 'core' component is recommended as the minimum installation.

Use Space or Enter to select/deselect items.
Press <DONE> when finished to return to the ROCm Options menu.